Seminar Marks 100th Birth Anniversary of Late President
FUZHOU , November 19 ( Xinhua ) -- East China 's Fujian Province hosted a seminar today on the thoughts of Liu Shaoqi and to mark the 100th birth anniversary of the late Chinese president .
Some 500 members of the provincial CPC Committee , government and People 's Liberation Army attended the event .
Liu is recognized as a great proletarian revolutionary , statesman , and an outstanding leader of the Communist Party of China ( CPC ) and the People 's Republic of China .
Liu was born in Ningxiang County , Hunan Province , on November 24 , 1898 .
He served as the president of in the late 1950s and early 1960s , and was widely recognized as a " civil servant who wholeheartedly served the people wholeheartedly " and contributed to China 's revolution and construction .
The late president was subjected to severe persecution during the Cultural Revolution .
Fujian is where Liu worked as secretary of the provincial CPC Committee in the 1930s .
